---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Vote" description="Campaign and manifesto page.">
  <section class="vote-page">
    <section class="vote-cta">
      <a
        class="vote-button"
        href="https://www.totum.vote/manmet"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer"
      >
        Vote Now
      </a>
      <p class="vote-countdown" id="vote-countdown" data-target="2026-04-14T23:59:59+01:00">
        13 days
      </p>
      <p class="vote-deadline">Voting ends April 14</p>
      <div class="vote-instructions">
        <p>Make sure to Join the MSSA through MMU Student Union.</p>
        <p>
          <a
            href="https://www.theunionmmu.org/groups/manchester-student-society-of-architecture-mssa"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >
            https://www.theunionmmu.org/groups/manchester-student-society-of-architecture-mssa
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="pillars">
      <h1><span class="lead-word">Better</span><span class="main-word">Portfolios</span></h1>
      <h1><span class="lead-word">Stronger</span><span class="main-word">Networks</span></h1>
      <h1><span class="lead-word">More</span><span class="main-word">Internships</span></h1>
    </section>

    <section class="candidates">
      <article class="candidate">
        <div class="portrait">
          <img class="portrait-image" src="/images/sebastian-chair.jpg" alt="Sebastian portrait" />
        </div>
        <div class="candidate-heading">
          <h2>MSSA Chair</h2>
          <p class="candidate-name">Sebastian</p>
        </div>
        <div class="candidate-copy manifesto-copy">
          <p>
            Through being leader of MSSA Climate Action Group, as well as creative
            director of MSSA photography, I am confident that I can benefit the role
            of MSSA Chair in every scale, for the individual student, for our community,
            and for how we present ourselves and collaborate with the world beyond the school.
            If you have met me, you know I am outgoing and friendly; always happy to talk
            and help you. As chair, some of my current goals are to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Involve the architecture staff / professors within MSSA subgroups through architecture competitions with students and teachers in teams.</li>
            <li>Give the ability for connectivity through a more rigorous interactive online website.</li>
            <li>Collaborate with cross faculties from both Universities MMU and UoM for inter curricular events specifically with the visual arts faculty and civil engineering faculty.</li>
            <li>Clear information and liaison between what students actually want vs what they are offered in the MSSA.</li>
            <li>Societies made accessible through defined calendars and schedules for friendly tournaments for the sports and clear events and incentives for the students.</li>
            <li>Quantitative outputs that result in verifiable and CV transferable experiences from MSSA to boost student employability.</li>
            <li>Direct relation with companies to boost and fast track active participants of the MSSA for summer or easter architecture internships.</li>
            <li>Greater reach for architecture companies, guest speakers and industry opportunities, for real networking.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Vote for Sebastian for MSSA to experience, grow and perform.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="candidate">
        <div class="portrait">
          <img
            class="portrait-image portrait-image--secretary"
            src="/images/ansh-secretary-V2.JPG"
            alt="Ansh portrait"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="candidate-heading">
          <h2>MSSA Secretary</h2>
          <p class="candidate-name">Ansh</p>
        </div>
        <div class="candidate-copy manifesto-copy">
          <p>
            Hi, I'm Ansh (Ash), a BA2 student, currently the Co-Lead of EDI Fora,
            and an Events Coordinator for MSSA IDesign. Through these roles, I've
            worked with students across different backgrounds, year groups, and
            interests, helping create a more inclusive and engaging environment;
            and now I am running for MSSA Secretary/Inclusions Officer, and I'm
            excited to contribute more actively and apply my leadership skills to
            a wider community.
          </p>
          <p>
            As an active member of MSA, I've seen how strong MSSA is as a platform
            for connection, collaboration, and student engagement. Building on the
            momentum of the previous committees, I want to help it grow into a
            space where every student feels welcomed, represented, and encouraged
            to take part.
          </p>
          <p>My Vision</p>
          <p>Stronger Connections</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Peer support networks across year groups.</li>
            <li>Cross-year discussions and informal crits.</li>
            <li>Student-staff-industry interaction.</li>
            <li>Collaboration across societies and subgroups.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Greater Inclusivity</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Low-pressure, welcoming social spaces.</li>
            <li>Events reflecting diverse cultures and interests.</li>
            <li>Encouraging participation from all students.</li>
            <li>Inclusive planning and accessibility in events.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>More Opportunities</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Alumni engagement and networking sessions.</li>
            <li>Workshops, studio visits, and collaborations.</li>
            <li>Support for portfolio and skill development.</li>
            <li>Clearer communication of opportunities.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Why Me?</p>
          <p>
            I am approachable, proactive, and committed to representing student
            voices. Through EDI Fora and MSSA IDesign, I've developed strong skills
            in inclusion, communication, and community-building; and if you know me,
            you know I'm always up for a conversation. I want to help create an
            MSSA that works for everyone, not just a few.
          </p>
          <p>Vote for Ansh to see 'your MSSA' grow.</p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="shared-manifesto">
      <p class="shared-label">Shared Manifesto</p>
      <div class="shared-copy shared-copy-block manifesto-copy">
        <p>
          Together, we want MSSA to be more connected and more ambitious in what it
          offers students. Our aim is to strengthen the sense of community within MSA
          while also expanding the opportunities, networks, and collaborations available
          through student life.
        </p>
        <p>
          We believe MSSA should not only bring people together socially, but also act
          as a stronger platform for participation, visibility, and growth. Connecting
          students across year groups, disciplines, and backgrounds, while opening
          clearer pathways to creative collaboration, industry engagement, and wider
          opportunity.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our shared vision is for an MSSA that feels welcoming and representative, but
          also active, outward-looking, and genuinely valuable: a society that helps
          students connect, contribute, and grow both within the school and beyond it.
        </p>
        <p>Vote Sebastian &amp; Ash for a more connected and ambitious MSSA.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<script is:inline>
  const countdown = document.getElementById('vote-countdown');

  if (countdown instanceof HTMLElement) {
    const target = new Date(countdown.dataset.target ?? '').getTime();

    const renderCountdown = () => {
      const now = Date.now();
      const distance = Math.max(target - now, 0);

      const days = Math.floor(distance / (1000 * 60 * 60 * 24));
      countdown.textContent = `${days} days`;
    };

    renderCountdown();
    window.setInterval(renderCountdown, 1000);
  }
</script>

<style>
  .vote-page {
    --manifesto-copy-size: clamp(13.125rem, 23.625vw, 16.40625rem);
    --shared-manifesto-copy-size: calc(var(--manifesto-copy-size) * 1.1);
    --divider-space: 5.15625rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--divider-space);
    margin: 0 auto;
    max-width: 64rem;
    padding: 5rem 0;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .pillars {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    text-align: center;
  }

  .pillars h1 {
    align-items: baseline;
    color: var(--ink);
    display: flex;
    font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    gap: 0.22em;
    justify-content: center;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .lead-word {
    color: rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.78);
    font-size: calc(20pt - 5pt);
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .main-word {
    font-size: 20pt;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .candidates {
    align-items: start;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.12);
    display: grid;
    gap: 3rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    padding-top: var(--divider-space);
  }

  .candidate {
    --profile-size: clamp(10rem, 18vw, 12.5rem);
    align-items: center;
    align-self: start;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    justify-content: flex-start;
    justify-self: center;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .candidate-heading {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0;
    justify-items: center;
  }

  .portrait {
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    background: rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.14);
    border-radius: 50%;
    overflow: hidden;
    width: var(--profile-size);
  }

  .portrait-image {
    display: block;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center 38%;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .portrait-image--secretary {
    object-position: center 54%;
    transform: scale(1.08);
    transform-origin: center 54%;
  }

  .candidate h2 {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.1vw, 1.75rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .candidate-name {
    color: rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.78);
    font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: 15pt;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .candidate-copy,
  .shared-copy {
    color: rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.78);
    font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11.25pt;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
    text-align: center;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .candidate-copy {
    width: var(--manifesto-copy-size);
  }

  .candidate-copy p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .manifesto-copy {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .manifesto-copy ul {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.7rem;
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.15rem;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .manifesto-copy li {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .shared-copy {
    width: var(--shared-manifesto-copy-size);
  }

  .shared-copy-block {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.9rem;
  }

  .shared-copy-block p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .shared-manifesto {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.12);
    display: grid;
    gap: 2rem;
    justify-items: center;
    padding-top: var(--divider-space);
    text-align: left;
  }

  .shared-label {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.1vw, 1.75rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0;
    text-align: center;
    width: var(--shared-manifesto-copy-size);
  }

  .vote-cta {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    justify-items: center;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .vote-button {
    border: 1px solid rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.2);
    color: var(--ink);
    display: inline-flex;
    font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    justify-content: center;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    min-width: 10rem;
    padding: 0.8rem 1.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background-color 180ms ease, border-color 180ms ease, color 180ms ease;
  }

  .vote-button:hover,
  .vote-button:focus-visible {
    background: rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.05);
    border-color: rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.32);
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .vote-countdown,
  .vote-deadline {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .vote-countdown {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2vw, 1.35rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .vote-deadline {
    color: rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.82);
    font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .vote-instructions {
    color: rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.78);
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.65rem;
    justify-items: center;
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
    max-width: 34rem;
  }

  .vote-instructions p {
    font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .vote-instructions a {
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-thickness: 0.05em;
    text-underline-offset: 0.12em;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .vote-page {
      gap: 4.5rem;
      padding: 4rem 0;
    }

    .pillars {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .candidates {
      gap: 3.5rem;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
